description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are recruiting for a Multi-skilled&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; Estates Maintenance Technician&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; having a Mechanical bias and knowledge of other trades.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will work within the Trust’s Maintenance team to carry out; equipment maintenance, installation work, inspections, testing, repairs and commissioning on a wide range of plant, equipment and services by conducting planned and reactive maintenance. The post holder will be required to participate in the Trusts out of hours’ on-call rota; all in accordance with the requirements and needs of the department, Trust and statutory procedures.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants need to have had substantial post qualification experience and have served a recognised apprenticeship or as a minimum NVQ level 3 or Equivalent City &amp; Guilds Qualification in a Mechanical Engineering qualification. The ability to fault find is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Experience working within the health service is not essential, however; you must be able to demonstrate cross trade multi-skilling. The successful applicant must have a broad working knowledge of mechanical systems, the ability to work from drawings and specifications without supervision, be computer literate and be able to work under pressure to meet the needs of the service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This role requires excellent communication skills as you will be liaising directly with clinical and non-clinical staff and service users. The post holder will have the skills to develop good working relationships in a multi-disciplinary team and have a strong commitment to delivering a professional service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The service covers the acute hospital site and various sites within the community; the Trust has a pool of vehicles for this purpose. Applicants must hold a full Driving Licence and have a willingness and ability to drive Trust vehicles, for travel between sites.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note interviews are due to be held week commencing the 30th November 2020.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working Hours: 37.5 hours per week.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;***Closing date is indicative only and this vacancy may close early without notice when sufficient applications have been received.***&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Andrew Haycock&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Deputy Head of Estates&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: andrew.haycock1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
